    {
      "id": "https://boingboing.net/2026/03/31/more-research-links-artificial-sweetener-erythritol-to-stroke-risk.html",
      "url": "https://boingboing.net/2026/03/31/more-research-links-artificial-sweetener-erythritol-to-stroke-risk.html",
      "title": "[Boing Boing] More research links artificial sweetener erythritol to stroke risk",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/shutterstock_158492423_bacho.jpg?fit=1800%2C1068&quality=60&ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/31/more-research-links-artificial-sweetener-erythritol-to-stroke-risk.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"More research links artificial sweetener erythritol to stroke risk\"><img alt=\"Photo: Bacho / Shutterstock. lllo: Beschizza\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"1068\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/shutterstock_158492423_bacho.jpg?fit=1800%2C1068&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1800\" /></a><p>Erythritol is widely used to sweeten sugar-free foods including snacks, drinks and energy bars. A zero-calorie sugar alcohol almost as sweet as sucrose, it doesn't spike blood sugar levels and is popular with low-carb dieters. But a recent study found that it <a href=\"https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/03/260328065333.htm\">might cause blood clots in the brain</a>, following on from <a href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41591-023-02223-9\">earlier research that associated it with a higher risk of heart attack or stroke.</a> &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/31/more-research-links-artificial-sweetener-erythritol-to-stroke-risk.html\">Read the rest </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/31/more-research-links-artificial-sweetener-erythritol-to-stroke-risk.html\">More research links artificial sweetener erythritol to stroke risk</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://boingboing.net\">Boing Boing</a>.</p>",
      "date_published": "2026-03-31T19:34:34+00:00",
      "authors": [
        {
          "name": "Boing Boing",
          "url": "https://boingboing.net/"
        }
      ],
      "image": "https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/shutterstock_158492423_bacho.jpg?fit=1800%2C1068&quality=60&ssl=1"
